    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - BATTERY, CHARGING AND CRANKING SYSTEMS -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Batteries And Cables
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Batteries And Cables</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The standard battery system for the 2554, 2654 and 4000 consist of two 12V maintenance-free batteries.
                Three 12V maintenance-free batteries are used in the 2574, 2674 and 8000. All optional batteries
                installed are also maintenance-free type.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When handling batteries, always wear face or eye protection, have water supply available,
                        assure good ventilation, and be sure no open flames are present.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823301">
            <title>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0823301">Battery Test Procedure</hotlnk>
            </title>
            <para>Test each battery separately.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect both battery terminal cables at each battery. Check each battery visually.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Examine the hydrometer eye (if no eye go to next step).</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Eye shows green - go to step 4.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Eye shows dark - recharge, then go to step 4.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Eye shows yellow - replace battery.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a 300A load for 15 seconds. Turn off load and wait one minute.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If 12.4V or more - go to step 4.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If less than 12.4V - recharge, then repeat step 3.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a test load equal to 50% of the battery CCA rating at 17.8&#176;C (0&#176;F).
                    After 15 seconds,
                    <emph type="bold">with the load still applied</emph>, measure and record terminal voltage ________.
                    Turn the load off.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Estimate the battery temperature. If measured voltage does not meet or exceed the value
                    shown in the following table, replace the battery.
                </para>
